    <rect x="20" y="161" width="660" height="36" rx="8" fill="#3f3f46"/>
    <text x="350" y="185" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">Around March 2026: ~4%</text>
    <rect x="20" y="204" width="660" height="44" rx="8" fill="#38bdf8" opacity="0.9"/>
    <text x="350" y="231" fill="#111113" font-size="14" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">July 2026 (now): 21.26% -- up more than 5x in four months</text>

    <text x="20" y="285" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13">2. Default OP_RETURN relay limit, Core vs. Knots</text>
    <rect x="20" y="298" width="320" height="70" rx="8" fill="#3f3f46"/>
    <text x="180" y="325" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">Core v30</text>
    <text x="180" y="349" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">83 bytes -&gt; 100,000 bytes</text>
    <rect x="360" y="298" width="320" height="70" rx="8" fill="#f87171" opacity="0.9"/>
    <text x="520" y="325" fill="#111113" font-size="13" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">Knots</text>
    <text x="520" y="349" fill="#111113" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">Strictly capped at 42 bytes</text>

    <text x="20" y="405" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13">3. Is this a protocol split (hard fork)?</text>
    <rect x="20" y="418" width="660" height="56" rx="8" fill="#3f3f46"/>
    <text x="350" y="440" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">No -- Core and Knots share identical consensus rules; OP_RETURN is relay-only</text>
    <text x="350" y="462" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">Knots nodes still validate and accept blocks containing large OP_RETURN data</text>

    <text x="350" y="590" fill="#52525b" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">Sources: Unchained, Bitcoin.com News, Bitcoin Magazine, OAK Research (as of July 14, 2026)</text>
  </g>
</svg>
